Essar Awaits Zimbabwe Go-Ahead for Steel Plant, NewsDay Reports

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 
2011-09-23T08:24:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/essar-awaits-zimbabwe-go-ahead-for-steel-plant-newsday-reports.html
Essar Africa Holdings Ltd., a unit
of Essar Group, is waiting for  Zimbabwe ’s government to transfer
mineral and ownership rights before starting operations, NewsDay
reported, citing a company official.  The company is ready to start once the government transfers
ownership of the Ziscosteel plant and associated mineral rights,
the Harare-based newspaper said, citing Firdhose Coovadia,
Essar’s Middle East and Africa resident director.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
 gmarawanyika@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
